      • updateEntity

        public abstract AgileEntity updateEntity(java.lang.String agileProjectValue,
                                         java.lang.String entityType,
                                         AgileEntity entity,
                                         ValueSet instanceConfigurationParameters)
        Update an agile entity in the agile tool. The only important fields to populate returned AgileEntityBean with are ID, URL, and lastUpdatedTime (post update, according to the agile tool).
        Parameters:
        agileProjectValue - the agile project information that was passed in the value of the AgileProject returned in IntegrationConnector.getAgileProjects(ValueSet).
        entityType - the type of entity (story, feature, ...). See getAgileEntitiesInfo(String, ValueSet)
        entity - an agile entity
        instanceConfigurationParameters - a value set which contains the configuration information of the instance
        Returns:
        An AgileEntityBean containing the information of the updated entity. The only important fields to provide are ID, URL, and lastUpdatedTime (post update, according to the agile tool).

      • postDeleteRequest

        public void postDeleteRequest(java.lang.String agileProjectValue,
                              java.lang.String entityType,
                              ValueSet instanceConfigurationParameters,
                              java.lang.String entityId)
        Do some operation in the agile tool if the related ppm request has been deleted. Default implementation does nothing.
        Parameters:
        agileProjectValue - the agile project information that was passed in the value of the AgileProject returned in IntegrationConnector.getAgileProjects(ValueSet).
        entityType - the type of entity (story, feature, ...). See getAgileEntitiesInfo(String, ValueSet)
        instanceConfigurationParameters - a value set which contains the configuration information of the connector instance
        entityId - the ID of the agile entity that is synched with the PPM Request that was deleted.
